We expect more than 20 mm of rain an hour.

42
00:03:29,023 --> 00:03:31,210
Dayo-chan!
[Man-san]

43
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:32,702
Yeah?

44
00:03:35,465 --> 00:03:38,093
Did you see Segasaki-san today?

45
00:03:38,093 --> 00:03:41,388
Yeah, five times. I'm still watching now.

46
00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:44,349
You really like him, huh?

47
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:46,320
I don't.

48
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:48,336
Then what?

49
00:03:49,755 --> 00:03:55,681
I like his facial structure the most out of everyone else in the world.

50
00:03:55,681 --> 00:03:58,606
It doesn't mean I like Segasaki Mizuki.

51
00:04:04,983 --> 00:04:07,196
Why? He's not just a pretty face.

52
00:04:07,196 --> 00:04:10,349
His smart way of speaking. His soft demeanor.

53
00:04:10,355 --> 00:04:15,260
Ever since he joined Everyday Weather, their viewership exploded 100-fold.

54
00:04:15,260 --> 00:04:19,258
I never thought I'd ever support a weatherman.

55
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:27,700
And that gentle smile.

56
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:30,544
My heart skips a beat.

57
00:04:31,189 --> 00:04:33,648
That's another thing I hate about him.

58
00:04:33,648 --> 00:04:37,444
You love him if you're watching him six times.

59
00:04:37,444 --> 00:04:41,150
Why're you dragging him through the mud like that?

60
00:04:41,150 --> 00:04:45,257
It feels more like you're just proactively criticizing me.

61
00:04:45,257 --> 00:04:48,596
Stop complaining, you confusing nerd.

62
00:04:48,596 --> 00:04:50,773
Sorry, I'm so confused.

63
00:04:58,649 --> 00:05:03,330
Hey, how's work going, Dayo-chan? Are you okay?

64
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:08,470
Well, yeah, I guess. Not sure.

65
00:05:08,470 --> 00:05:12,710
What? Are you allowed to talk about it?

66
00:05:13,970 --> 00:05:16,529
Well, I have time until the deadline.

67
00:05:16,529 --> 00:05:19,860
But to answer your question...

68
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:23,395
I don't think my work's going to sell.

69
00:05:23,395 --> 00:05:26,283
Sorry for the weird question.

70
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:33,652
The reviews from my work last month were crazy.

71
00:05:33,652 --> 00:05:35,185
People can't get enough.

72
00:05:35,185 --> 00:05:38,318
Stop. Don't pour salt on your own wound.

73
00:05:38,318 --> 00:05:43,740
And my editor hasn't been calling as much lately.

74
00:05:44,635 --> 00:05:46,411
You're just freaking yourself out.

75
00:05:46,411 --> 00:05:47,833
I mean...

76
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,420
That's not convincing.

77
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:51,320
Hey.

78
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:54,186
You're calling a girl again?

79
00:05:56,205 --> 00:05:58,663
Didn't you hear me come home?

80
00:06:01,232 --> 00:06:03,085
Welcome home.

81
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:05,840
I need food.

82
00:06:16,795 --> 00:06:20,571
Does he not know how to say "Thank you"?

83
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:36,440
Unfortunately, this man isn't a Segasaki Mizuki look-alike or his twin.

84
00:06:38,033 --> 00:06:40,804
It's actually him.

85
00:06:44,681 --> 00:06:46,881
What do you say?

86
00:06:46,881 --> 00:06:49,980
He used to be my Senpai in college.

87
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:51,780
What?

88
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:53,628
Like I said,

89
00:06:53,628 --> 00:06:56,607
you should keep doing manga.

90
00:06:56,607 --> 00:06:59,706
I can give you food, water, and shelter.

91
00:06:59,706 --> 00:07:01,615
So, live with me.

92
00:07:06,055 --> 00:07:08,080
What's for dinner?

93
00:07:08,914 --> 00:07:11,847
It's... stir-fried pork with ginger.

94
00:07:17,404 --> 00:07:19,162
Hey.

95
00:07:21,117 --> 00:07:23,207
Who was that woman?

96
00:07:24,804 --> 00:07:26,829
"That woman"?

97
00:07:26,829 --> 00:07:29,681
The one you always call.

98
00:07:29,681 --> 00:07:32,993
An otaku friend.

99
00:07:33,831 --> 00:07:35,631
Oh, really?

100
00:07:41,017 --> 00:07:43,604
Don't ask if you don't care.

101
00:08:11,308 --> 00:08:13,345
It's bland.

102
00:08:13,996 --> 00:08:15,696
Soy sauce.

103
00:08:23,229 --> 00:08:24,729
Sorry.

104
00:09:28,793 --> 00:09:30,493
All right then.

105
00:09:33,399 --> 00:09:36,767
Hm? What is it?

106
00:09:39,287 --> 00:09:40,887
Nothing.

107
00:09:48,311 --> 00:09:49,811
Bed time.

108
00:09:51,097 --> 00:09:53,821
Oh, okay.

109
00:09:53,821 --> 00:09:56,440
- Good night.
- Okay.

110
00:09:58,515 --> 00:10:00,885
What? Is he sick?

111
00:10:00,885 --> 00:10:03,981
Is he only able to say two-word sentences?

112
00:10:07,646 --> 00:10:11,118
He keeps getting too close to me.

113
00:10:12,458 --> 00:10:17,743
It'll stop raining in many areas, but the humidity will still haunt the Kanto region.

114
00:10:17,743 --> 00:10:21,599
- I get so annoyed every day.
- This will keep the clouds around,

115
00:10:21,599 --> 00:10:25,240
causing it to rain in the Tokyo city area.

116
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:28,152
Don't forget your umbrella.

117
00:10:31,356 --> 00:10:35,358
The weather's all I watch every day.

118
00:11:07,232 --> 00:11:09,352
From now on,

119
00:11:09,352 --> 00:11:11,792
we'll do it on sunny days.

120
00:11:11,792 --> 00:11:13,677
Be prepared.

121
00:11:22,281 --> 00:11:25,851
It's been raining a lot.

122
00:11:45,514 --> 00:11:49,608
It's a given that everybody hates the rain.

123
00:11:51,926 --> 00:11:55,614
It's humid and feels gross.

124
00:11:56,748 --> 00:12:00,035
That's why I also...

125
00:12:00,638 --> 00:12:02,936
Is breakfast ready?

126
00:12:02,936 --> 00:12:05,646
- I'll go make some now.
- Okay.

127
00:12:14,458 --> 00:12:19,738
I can't help but get annoyed about small things like this too.

128
00:12:21,387 --> 00:12:25,343
Now let's take a look at the Kanto region.

129
00:12:25,343 --> 00:12:29,746
The weather's making a comeback. It'll be sunny all day.

130
00:12:29,746 --> 00:12:31,567
- Perfect for laundry.
- Sunny?

131
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:33,762
The humidity all across Japan will fall,

132
00:12:33,762 --> 00:12:37,268
- making it a comfortable day.
- That's right.

133
00:12:37,268 --> 00:12:42,648
I'm the only one in the world who'd think "sunny" is a dirty word.

134
00:12:42,648 --> 00:12:47,600
The continuing rain is expected to continue late into the night.

135
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:51,235
It will clear tomorrow morning depending on the southern waters.

136
00:12:51,235 --> 00:12:54,382
The high pressure will clear the rain clouds...

137
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:12,417
[Segasaki Mizuki: Curry]

138
00:13:15,045 --> 00:13:18,054
He doesn't understand.

139
00:13:18,054 --> 00:13:20,574
He wouldn't get how it feels.

140
00:13:22,112 --> 00:13:25,925
I have to go back to the market in the rain because of that one word.

141
00:13:25,925 --> 00:13:28,925
That empty feeling when I buy the curry roux.

142
00:13:30,034 --> 00:13:34,989
The lady's one-sided discomfort when she sees me back again.

143
00:13:48,195 --> 00:13:52,330
In the end, I hate how obedient I am.

144
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:04,962
What? Seafood?

145
00:14:04,962 --> 00:14:07,179
I wanted pork.

146
00:14:14,404 --> 00:14:16,004
How much longer?

147
00:14:17,187 --> 00:14:20,400
It'll be done cooking soon.

148
00:14:21,290 --> 00:14:22,690
Okay.

149
00:14:28,588 --> 00:14:30,644
It's sunny tomorrow.

150
00:14:32,574 --> 00:14:37,167
It's sunny, so he'll sleep with me when he's full.

151
00:14:52,723 --> 00:14:54,223
I need sauce.

152
00:14:55,053 --> 00:14:57,340
Okay.

153
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:27,052
Our time at dinner is the same as yesterday.

154
00:15:27,857 --> 00:15:31,081
His attitude is the same as yesterday.

155
00:15:32,450 --> 00:15:33,950
But...

156
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:03,048
Wait, I'm doing the dishes.

157
00:16:03,048 --> 00:16:04,648
No.

158
00:16:21,225 --> 00:16:24,049
We have sex when it's sunny.

159
00:16:27,936 --> 00:16:33,350
The word "sunny" wouldn't make you think

160
00:16:33,350 --> 00:16:35,910
of having sex on a humid night,

161
00:16:42,128 --> 00:16:48,023
but it's cemented in my mind as a dirty word.

162
00:16:49,510 --> 00:16:54,110
Do you understand how I feel when the forecast

163
00:16:54,110 --> 00:16:56,890
comes out of your mouth?

164
00:16:56,890 --> 00:16:58,728
What are you doing?

165
00:17:19,332 --> 00:17:21,481
I bet you don't.

166
00:17:22,156 --> 00:17:25,043
I bet you'll never think about it.

167
00:17:27,567 --> 00:17:28,967
Hey.

168
00:17:30,994 --> 00:17:32,694
Open your mouth.

169
00:17:35,543 --> 00:17:37,643
More.

170
00:17:37,646 --> 00:17:39,525
After all...

171
00:17:39,525 --> 00:17:42,050
We're not even lovers,

172
00:17:43,390 --> 00:17:46,140
yet you're completely fine with this.

173
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:02,222
I'm already bound to him as his slave.

174
00:18:02,222 --> 00:18:05,525
It's natural that I obey his voice.

175
00:18:05,525 --> 00:18:08,878
I have no choice.

176
00:18:11,209 --> 00:18:12,709
But...

177
00:18:21,866 --> 00:18:24,815
Why is it only before a sunny day?

178
00:19:10,516 --> 00:19:14,402
So you're a professional manga artist?

179
00:19:14,402 --> 00:19:16,189
Why are you quitting?

180
00:19:18,369 --> 00:19:20,742
I'm not popular.

181
00:19:20,742 --> 00:19:23,189
I can't make a living.

182
00:19:23,189 --> 00:19:25,690
I have to find a job.

183
00:19:26,312 --> 00:19:28,280
Hm, but that's no fun.

184
00:19:31,372 --> 00:19:33,942
You don't want to quit, right?

185
00:19:36,584 --> 00:19:38,084
Yes.

186
00:19:40,679 --> 00:19:42,178
Then...

187
00:19:43,324 --> 00:19:45,019
Come live with me.

188
00:19:45,019 --> 00:19:47,994
I'm planning on making some good money.

189
00:19:54,168 --> 00:19:55,921
What do you say?

190
00:19:57,665 --> 00:19:59,165
What?

191
00:20:00,874 --> 00:20:03,274
Like I said,

192
00:20:03,274 --> 00:20:06,205
you should keep doing manga.

193
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:09,126
I can give you food, water, and shelter.

194
00:20:09,126 --> 00:20:11,111
So, live with me.

195
00:20:13,561 --> 00:20:17,085
And in exchange...

196
00:20:18,452 --> 00:20:21,094
Do everything I say.

197
00:20:30,072 --> 00:20:31,701
What do you say?

198
00:20:35,786 --> 00:20:37,878
Three years have passed.

199
00:21:17,901 --> 00:21:19,854
Don't lose your way.

200
00:21:28,190 --> 00:21:32,991
Yoh, I'm coming home late, so I won't need dinner.

201
00:21:32,991 --> 00:21:34,567
Okay.

202
00:21:43,684 --> 00:21:48,247
We're here for the next three hours on Everyday Weather. I'm Takatsu Reiko.

203
00:21:48,247 --> 00:21:52,485
I'm meteorologist Segasaki Mizuki.

204
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:56,466
An update from the Meteorological Agency.

205
00:21:56,466 --> 00:22:00,760
Both East and West Japan have entered the rainy season.

206
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:04,156
Did you know that the type of rain differs in each region,

207
00:22:04,156 --> 00:22:06,834
- even during the rainy season?
- What?

208
00:22:06,834 --> 00:22:12,018
- West Japan has heavy showers, 
- It can't be true.

209
00:22:12,018 --> 00:22:13,800
while East Japan

210
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:18,760
has comparatively mild rain.

211
00:22:18,761 --> 00:22:21,796
We've adopted a new system.

212
00:22:21,796 --> 00:22:27,411
We have improved our ability to check global warming trends.

213
00:22:27,411 --> 00:22:30,051
- Next. 
- That means...

214
00:22:31,506 --> 00:22:36,212
we won't... do it for a while.

215
00:22:41,076 --> 00:22:43,637
I don't have to do it for a while.

216
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:49,830
♫ I accidentally think back to that day and
my chest tightens painfully ♫

217
00:22:49,830 --> 00:22:55,260
♫ If this feeling has a name ♫

218
00:22:55,260 --> 00:22:57,880
♫ Why don't you tell me about it, so I can understand? ♫

219
00:22:57,880 --> 00:23:00,560
♫ A sultry night that seems endless ♫

220
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:05,620
♫ I hope I will get through it alone ♫

221
00:23:05,620 --> 00:23:08,290
♫ The more you put it into words ♫

222
00:23:08,290 --> 00:23:11,810
♫ The more my heart vanishes ♫

223
00:23:11,810 --> 00:23:18,940
♫ I want you to feel the body warmth that touches you ♫

224
00:23:18,940 --> 00:23:23,650
♫ The time we spend together ♫

225
00:23:23,650 --> 00:23:30,640
♫ I had hoped it would last forever ♫

226
00:23:30,648 --> 00:23:33,928
[Preview]
It's been a while, isn't it?

227
00:23:33,928 --> 00:23:35,777
You don't have to do it for a while.

228
00:23:35,777 --> 00:23:37,770
Are you working overtime today?

229
00:23:37,770 --> 00:23:41,443
Hey, what is it, tell me, what is it?

230
00:23:41,443 --> 00:23:43,856
Open-chested clothes every time!

231
00:23:43,856 --> 00:23:46,442
Is this some sort of erotic disaster?

232
00:23:46,442 --> 00:23:48,475
I can't help it!

233
00:23:48,475 --> 00:23:50,712
Don't take it for granted.

234
00:23:50,712 --> 00:23:55,453
You don't love me. I am only a convenient tool to you.

235
00:23:55,453 --> 00:23:59,853
I've never been laughed at like that.
